wikipedia_page.main: Tommy Tickler (30 September 1852 – 19 January 1938) was an English businessman and Conservative Party politician from Grimsby in Lincolnshire.

response: *Early possibilities to be the Unionist candidate included former Brigg MP Sir Berkeley Sheffield and local party chairman RW Roberts."Death Of Sir G. Doughty." Times [London, England] 28 April 1914: 10. The Times Digital Archive. Web. 2 March 2014. On 30 April jam manufacturer Thomas Tickler was chosen by the Unionists as their candidate to defend the seat. He was a local JP and Town Councillor, having served as Mayor in 1907."News in Brief." Times [London, England] 1 May 1914: 8. The Times Digital Archive. Web. 2 March 2014.
